                <ol class="pt-3">
                    <li>Each paper accepted for presentation in CICT 2020 has to be registered under any one of the
                        categories â€“ Industry/ Academia or Student. The presenter will present the paper virtually
                        during the allotted slot as per the Technical Program Schedule.</li>
                    <li>A student can register at the Student rate to become a Presenter. However, such papers will
                        not be part of the Conference Proceedings and will not be submitted for indexing in IEEE Xplore
                        Digital Library.
                    </li>
                    <li>Papers which are registered at the regular rate of Academia / Industry category and presented
                        virtually during the allotted slot as per the Technical Program Schedule are eligible for
                        inclusion in the Conference Proceedings and submission for indexing in IEEE Xplore Digital
                        Library.</li>
                    <li>The authors of papers mentioned in point no.3 have to submit the camera-ready version as per
                        IEEE Guidelines which will be included in the Conference Proceedings to be indexed in IEEE
                        Xplore Digital Library. The detailed instructions for camera-ready paper submission will be
                        communicated shortly. The papers will appear in IEEE Xplore Digital Library subject to the IEEE
                        guidelines and copyright formalities. IEEE reserves the right to exclude a paper from
                        distribution after the conference (e.g., removal from IEEE Xplore) if the paper is not presented
                        by an author at the conference.</li>
                    <li>If an author has more than one accepted paper, registration at Academia / Industry Rate is
                        required to be done only for one paper. The second paper can be registered at the student rate
                        if the paper has student authors. However, if the second paper does not have student authors,
                        then it shall also be registered at the Academia/Industry rate.</li>
                </ol>
